-- Serena Williams and Azarenka Advance to U.S. Open Women’s Final
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-09-07T22:57:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/serena-williams-and-azarenka-advance-to-u-s-open-women-s-final.html
Three-time champion  Serena Williams 
advanced to the U.S. Open women’s final with a 6-1, 6-2 defeat
of Italy’s Sara Errani and will play top-seeded Victoria
Azarenka of Belarus for the title.  Williams, 30, the fourth seed from the U.S., had 38 winners
compared to six for her 10th-seeded opponent.  Azarenka, 23, defeated third-seeded Maria Sharapova of
Russia in three sets to reach her first U.S. Open final.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  